A simple deathmatch map for short/mid and long range target practice.
The map itself is big, Could be good for large servers. Recommended to add more spawn locations if you have more then 32 players.
The CSSDM spawn file is included in the package, which contains 34 spawn locations.

Have Fun

This is my first ever, completely developed CS:S map. Like the name implies, it is set inside of a missile silo. One of the most unique aspects, and probably the most important one, is that the missile can be launched from a control panel in a side room, which will kill anyone within the blast radius. Boxes are  also spread around in the hallways to provide some cover. Up to 32 players can play.

I hope you can enjoy it as much as I had fun making it. Enjoy! :)

Another small map, 6 spawn points for each team. The map is best played with 3 players on each team, also it has a full nav. file so you can play it with bots (they do however love to camp near the spawn points) no radar image though, I still don't know how to do that... I tryed using cubemaps so you won't really see any shadows I think, though the map looks nice and shiny. The screenshots don't show the map's shiny, clean look.

Can't find any bugs, if you do find any, post a comment or just send me a message.

Any sugestions about improvements, critics and "you suck" comments are welcome, I'm here to learn so, go ahead. If I think there are a few changes needed to be done, I'll try to improve the map. Don't forget to rate ;)

I don't feel like talking too much so that's about it. 

PS: The map has a little easter egg, have fun.

Thank you for taking your time downlaoding and adding your input. I want to make this map as fun and accurate as possible. This is my first map and I am interested in fidning a partner to work with to reach my goal of brining a piece of Metal Gear Solid to Counter-Strike: Source. Thank you for reading.

Happy Halloween 2010! (quite late though)

This map is the CS:S version of the TF2 map I released a month earlier. Sorry for the delay.

I can gladly call it my "biggest map" in terms of size but also in terms of content. Thanks to the Halloween 2010 TF2 update, I've got a bunch of new props to put in my mansion. This version isn't focused on CS:S pro gameplay, firstly because it was designed for TF2 initially, think of it as a map for having fun like MarioKart. This way, I could add a lot more rooms and features. It will take you some time to find every secret of this map, will you find the 6 paintings and reach the "map maker's room" ? Or will you keep falling in Flandre's traps until the end of time?

the map's weight is due to the TF2 props not being into CS:S (obviously) though the original version was already quite heavy. I couldn't make this version's custom content fit in the .bsp with pakrat.

BE CAREFUL! This map contains Sakuya Brando, Vuvuzelas, Bodied Yukkuri Remirya, Flandre's secret training yard, So Nanoka?, and a bunch of other things, dangerous or not...and also, a BRAND NEW TRAP TO REPLACE the Horseless Headless Horseman one

since the map was for TF2, everything might looks bigger than it should.
